Mexican Stocks: Alfa, Grupo Televisa, Walmex Shares Declines

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n   a n d   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 
2011-04-07T21:53:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-07/mexican-stocks-televisa-walmex-shares-decline-bolsa-gains.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IPC index fell 1 percent to 37,471.54.  Alfa SAB (ALFAA MM), the world’s largest producer of
aluminum engine heads, fell 2.6 percent to 163.93 pesos, its
first decline in seven trading days. Before today, Alfa had
gained 35 percent since the end of 2010 compared to a 7 percent
decline for the IPC Index.  Grupo Televisa SA (TLEVICPO)  , the world’s largest
Spanish-language broadcaster, declined 4.5 percent to 54.15
pesos, its lowest price since Oct. 12 and largest one-day
decline since April 27. Televisa agreed to buy a 50 percent
stake in Grupo Iusacell SA for $1.6 billion, entering Mexico’s
wireless market, the company said in a statement today to the
Mexican stock exchange.  Wal-Mart de Mexico SAB (WALMEXV MM) slipped 1 percent to
35.31 pesos. Latin America’s largest retailer said same-store
sales fell 1.1 percent in March from the same period last year,
according to a statement to the Mexican stock exchange.  To contact the reporters on this story:
